Q: Schema validation failed with the following errors in Angular project A: <p>Your <code>serve</code> section is missing <code>buildTarget</code> at the options level. In Angular 20's dev-server, it's now required there and not just inside configurations.</p>
<p>Add an <code>options</code> block to your serve:</p>
<pre><code>&quot;serve&quot;: {
  &quot;builder&quot;: &quot;@angular/build:dev-server&quot;,
  &quot;options&quot;: {
    &quot;buildTarget&quot;: &quot;users-app:build&quot;
  },
  &quot;configurations&quot;: {
    &quot;production&quot;: {
      &quot;buildTarget&quot;: &quot;users-app:build:production&quot;
    },
    &quot;development&quot;: {
      &quot;buildTarget&quot;: &quot;users-app:build:development&quot;,
      &quot;port&quot;: 4201
    }
  },
  &quot;defaultConfiguration&quot;: &quot;development&quot;
}
</code></pre>
<p>If your other project works without this, it's probably running on cached/older node_modules. Eventually it'll hit the same issue.</p>
<p>And yeah, nuking <code>node_modules</code> and <code>package-lock.json</code> then running <code>npm i</code> fresh is worth doing anyway when chasing weird config errors, rules out stale packages.</p>
